{"source_key":"sha256-77a8d0a023ee41ad7912180250238aff","record_index":2645,"record_hash":"sha256:daa42086ec363546981786c438cf33973a02d9eb39e97501bde018e9263d3227","timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:59:29.144Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Found 3 worth fixing:\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs:86): Cross-clone duplicate capture can create duplicate turns. Path: clone A and clone B both capture the same previously unseen transcript before either syncs, both pass local `record-hashes`, both compute the same `turn_key`, but append separate `:turns` list entries. GitMeta list merge unions both entries, while `turn:<turn_key>` collapses to one detail, so `get_session_timeline()` can render the same turn twice and `list_sessions()` overcounts.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs:383): Duplicate-capture enrichment can attach the wrong repo state to an old turn. Path: first capture accepts records but environment is `failed/partial`; later, after branch/worktree state changes, the same transcript is captured with no new records; `enrich_incomplete_turn()` matches only by source and record hashes, then writes current `observed_targets` onto the old turn and indexes it. That can make `findRelatedSessions(branch/review/change)` return convincing but false evidence.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:170): Capture and association are not one failure boundary. Path: `record_agent_log()` validates the association target before the lock, then writes transcript metadata, then calls `associate_session()` as a separate GitMeta mutation. If association write fails, the command returns an error after persisting the session/turn/index batch, so retry semantics are messy: the retry reports `Captured 0 records...` even though the failed command already created durable capture state.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:59:29.144Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}